query: অর্ডোভিশিয়ান যুগের ঠিক পরের যুগের নাম কী ?
query_translated_en: What is the name of the period right after the Ordovician period? [b]
passage_in_language: অর্ডোভিশিয়ান হল পুরাজীব মহাযুগের দ্বিতীয় যুগ। এর সময়সীমা ছিল থেকে কোটি বছর আগে পর্যন্ত। এর পূর্ববর্তী যুগ ক্যাম্ব্রিয়ান এবং পরবর্তী যুগ সিলুরিয়ান। ১৮৭৯ খ্রিঃ বিজ্ঞানী অ্যাডাম সেজউইক এবং রডারিক মার্চিসন এই সময়কালের পাথরগুলিকে যথাক্রমে ক্যাম্ব্রিয়ান ও সিলুরিয়ান যুগের অন্তর্ভুক্ত বলে দাবি করলে বিবাদের সূচনা হয়। এই বিবাদ নিরসনের জন্য অন্যতম কেল্টীয় উপজাতি "অর্ডোভিশি"-দের নামানুসারে চার্লস ল্যাপওয়ার্থ নতুন একটি ভূতাত্ত্বিক যুগের ধারণা দেন। ল্যাপওয়ার্থ বুঝেছিলেন, বিতর্কিত পাথরের স্তরে প্রাপ্ত জীবাশ্মগুলি পূর্বোক্ত দুই যুগের কোনোটার সাথেই পুরোপুরি খাপ খায় না। যুক্তরাজ্যে চটজলদি অর্ডোভিশিয়ান যুগের স্বীকৃতি না মিললেও অবশিষ্ট বিশ্ব অবিলম্বেই এই ধারণা স্বীকার করে নেয়। ১৯৬০ খ্রিঃ অর্ডোভিশিয়ান আনুষ্ঠানিকভাবে আন্তর্জাতিক স্বীকৃতি লাভ
passage_en: The Ordovician is the second epoch of the Paleozoic Era. Its time span is from millions of years ago. Its earlier period is Cambrian and later period is Silurian. Controversy began in 1879 AD when scientists Adam Sedgwick and Roderick Murchison claimed that rocks from this period belonged to the Cambrian and Silurian periods respectively. To resolve this dispute, Charles Lapworth proposed a new geological age named after one of the Celtic tribes, the "Ordovici". Lapworth realized that the fossils found in the disputed rock strata did not fit neatly into either of the two aforementioned periods. Although the Ordovician age was not quickly accepted in the UK, the rest of the world soon accepted the idea. 1960 AD Ordovician officially received international recognition

query: ইখওয়ান দলটি কবে গঠিত হয় ?
query_translated_en: When was the Ikhwan party formed? [b]
passage_in_language: ইখওয়ান ( , "ভ্রাতৃত্ব") (আখওয়ান বলেও পরিচিত) ছিল একটি ওয়াহাবি মিলিশিয়া দল। এরা মূলত যাযাবর গোত্রীয় লোকদের নিয়ে গঠিত হয়। তারা ইবনে সৌদের পক্ষে গুরুত্বপূর্ণ সামরিক শক্তি হিসেবে কাজ করে এবং আধুনিক সৌদি আরব প্রতিষ্ঠায় ভূমিকা পালন করে। সর্বপ্রথম ১৯১৩ সালে ইখওয়ানরা আবির্ভূত হয়। বেদুইন গোষ্ঠীগুলোকে ভেঙে তাদের বিভিন্ন কূপ ও মরূদ্যানের আশেপাশে বসতি করার পরিকল্পনাকারী ওয়াহাবি ধর্মতাত্ত্বিকরা তাদের উদ্ভব ঘটান। তাদের দাবি ছিল যে যাযাবর জীবন ইসলাম অণুযায়ী জীবন যাপনের উপযুক্ত নয়। এসকল বেদুইন লোকেরা তাদের যাযাবর জীবন থেকে যোদ্ধা হিসেবে নিয়োগ পেত। ইখওয়ানের ধর্মীয় প্রধানরা ইসলামের বিশুদ্ধতা ও ঐক্যের প্রতি নিবেদিত ছিলেন। ইখওয়ানে যোগ দেয়া কিছু নতুন সদস্য
passage_en: The Ikhwan ( , "brotherhood") (also known as Akhwan) was a Wahhabi militia group. They are mainly made up of nomadic tribal people. They served as an important military force for Ibn Saud and played a role in the establishment of modern Saudi Arabia. The Ikhwans first appeared in 1913. They originated with Wahhabi theologians who planned to break up the Bedouin clans and settle around their various wells and oases. They claimed that the nomadic life was not suitable for living according to Islam. These Bedouin people were recruited as warriors from their nomadic life. The religious leaders of the Ikhwan were devoted to the purity and unity of Islam. Some new members joined the Ikhwan

query_translated_en: How many sub-divisions are there in North Twenty Four Parganas district of West Bengal? [b]
passage_in_language: উত্তর চব্বিশ পরগণা জেলা ভারত এর পূর্বাঞ্চলীয় রাজ্য পশ্চিমবঙ্গের কলকাতা শহরের উত্তরপূর্ব দিকের একটি জেলা। জেলাটি প্রেসিডেন্সি বিভাগের অন্তর্ভুক্ত। ১৯৮৩ সালে ডঃ অশোক মিত্রের প্রশাসনিক সংস্কার কমিটি এই জেলাকে বিভাজনের সুপারিশ করেন। ১৭ই ফাল্গুণ ১৩৯২ বঙ্গাব্দে (১৯৮৬ সালে ১লা মার্চ) ২৪ পরগণা জেলাটিকে দ্বিখণ্ডিত করে ওই জেলার উত্তরাংশ নিয়ে উত্তর ২৪ পরগণা জেলা স্থাপন করা হয়৷ এর প্রশাসনিক ভবন ও সদর দপ্তর বারাসাত শহরে অবস্থিত৷ বারাসাত, বারাকপুর, বনগাঁ, বসিরহাট, বিধাননগর এই পাঁচটি মহকুমা নিয়ে উত্তর ২৪ পরগণা জেলা গঠিত। ১৭৫৭ সালে বাংলার নবাব মীরজাফর কলকাতার দক্ষিণে কুলপি পর্যন্ত অঞ্চলে ২৪ টি জংলীমহল বা পরগনার জমিদারি সত্ত্ব ভোগ করার অধিকার দেন
passage_en: North Twenty-Four Parganas District is a district northeast of the city of Kolkata in the eastern state of West Bengal, India. The district belongs to the Presidency Division. In 1983, Dr. Ashok Mitra's Administrative Reforms Committee recommended the division of the district. On 17th Falguna 1392 Bangabd (1 March 1986), the 24 Parganas district was bifurcated and North 24 Parganas district was established with the northern part of the district. Its administrative building and headquarters are located in Barasat city Barasat, Barakpur, Bangaon, Basirhat, Bidhannagar are the five sub-divisions of North 24 Parganas district. In 1757, Nawab Mirzafar of Bengal granted 24 janglimahals or parganas of zamindari in the area south of Calcutta up to Kulpi.

passage_en: The Siachen Glacier is located in the eastern Karakoram range of the Himalayas, just east of the India-Pakistan Line of Control in latitude. At 21,000 feet above sea level, this glacier is the highest battlefield in the world. The flora and fauna of the Siachen region is influenced by the huge army here. Some rare species, such as the brown bear, are under threat due to the huge army here.

The reason for this name is that the rocks of this age were first discovered in Britain from the region of Wales, and the Latin name for Wales is "Cambria". The distinctive feature of the Cambrian rock strata is the extent of intervening lagasthetta silt deposits. passage_en: The White Dacha, (; ) is the house that Anton Chekhov had built in Yalta and in which he wrote some of his greatest work. It is now a writer's house museum. The White Dacha was built in 1898 following Chekhov's success with "The Seagull". He took up residence there after his father's death and to aid him with coping with tuberculosis. Chekhov planted a variety of trees including mulberry, cherry, almond, peach, cypress, citrus, acacia and birch. He also kept dogs and tame cranes. The house was designed by L.N. Shapovalov. passage_en: Snanayatra (Oriya: বানা জাত্র) is a festival organized on the Purnima Tithi of the first month of the Hindu calendar. It is an important festival for devotees of Hindu deity Jagannath. This day is considered as the birthday of Jagannath. Jagannath, Balabhadra, Subhadra, Sudarshana Chakra and Madanamohan idols are brought out from the Jagannath temple to the bathing altar on the occasion of Sannayatra in Puri. There they are ritually bathed and adorned in beautiful robes for the darshan of devotees. Devotees of Jagannath believe that if they visit the deity at the Jagannath temple in Puri on that day, they will be freed from all their sins. Solid gold and copper razors were also found in Ancient Egyptian tombs dating back to the 4th millennium BC. The first steel-edged cutthroat razors were manufactured in Sheffield in 1680. The administrative center is the city of Barasat. According to the 2011 census, it had a total population of 10,082,852 inhabitants, of whom 4,910,714 were women and 5,172,138 men.

passage_en: The Bhutanese Royal Court of Justice (Dzongkha: དཔལ་ལྡན་འབྲུག་པའི་དྲང་ཁྲིམས་ལྷན་སྡེ་; Wylie "Dpal-ldan 'Brug-pai Drang-khrims Lhan-sde"; Palden Drukpa Drangkhrim Lhende) is the government body which oversees the judicial system of Bhutan. Senior Judges of the courts are appointed by the monarch. Bhutan's legal system is influenced by English common law. The Royal Court of Justice is based in the capital Thimphu. The Bhutanese justice system has always suffered from a lack of qualified officers with most of the office-holders being civil servants. Until the passing of the National Judicial Service Act of 2007, Judges were still a part of the Bhutanese civil service.

passage_en: Ramakrishna (1836–1886) is a famous mystic of nineteenth-century India. Ramakrishna never wrote down the details of his own life. Sources for his life and teachings come from the writings of his disciples and live witnesses. Ramakrishna's recorded sayings mainly come from the last four years of his life. The book "Sri Sri Rāmakrishna Kathāmrita" by Mahendranath Gupta under the pseudonym "M.", was published in five volumes in 1902, 1905, 1908, 1910 and 1932. Mahendranath Gupta recorded his daily interactions with Ramakrishna in his diary which were subsequently published as "Sri-Sri-Ramakrishna-Kathamrta" in 5 Volumes in Bengali. passage_en: Joseph Smith Fletcher (7 February 1863 Halifax, West Yorkshire – 30 January 1935 Dorking, Surrey) was an English journalist and author. British mystery writer Joseph Smith Fletcher was born in Halifax, the son of a clergyman. He was orphaned by his father at the age of eight months. His grandmother, who lives in Darrington near Pontefract, took him to her farm to raise him. Joseph completed his qualifications at Silcoates School in Wakefield. At the age of 18, he moved to London to become a journalist. He worked in a few newspapers, although he was not yet a reporter. After studying law for a while, he started as an assistant editor at the age of 20. At times he returned to his native Yorkshire. He eventually ended up as a freelance writer. Fletcher married the Irish writer Rosamond Langbridge. The family had one son, Valentine Fletcher, who served as a priest in various parishes in Yorkshire

The genocide was carried out through physical extermination and deportation, including the displacement of the civilian population under conditions that lead to certain death. The Armenian Genocide was carried out in several stages: the disarmament of Armenian soldiers, the selective deportation of Armenians from the border regions, the adoption of the expulsion law, the mass deportation and the killing of Armenians. passage_en: The United Nations is an international organization created to maintain and strengthen international peace and security and develop cooperation between states. Согласно постановлению Милли Меджлиса (Национального Собрания) Азербайджанской Республики 26 февраля объявлено «Днем Ходжалинского геноцида и национального траура». passage_en: The Day of Remembrance of the Victims of Khojaly ("Day of the Khojaly genocide and national mourning") is a memorable date celebrated on February 26 in the Republic of Azerbaijan. passage_en: Andhra Vaidya College (English: Andhra Medical College) is an educational institution that was established in the year 1902 in the city of Visakhapatnam in the state of Andhra Pradesh to provide medical services to the coastal districts. Medical education in Visakhapatnam started at the beginning of the last century as the Victoria Diamond Jubilee Medical School in the year 1902. Maharaja Gode Narayana Gajapathi Rao and Maharani Chittijanakiamma helped establish it near the old post office. After some time the medical school was moved to the present physiology department. The course, which started with 50 students in the first batch, was called Licentiate Certificate Standard A. The school building was started as Vizagapatnam Medical College on 1st July, 1923 with 32 students. But the college started functioning on 7th July, 1923 with Captain Frederick Jasper Anderson as the Headmaster.

passage_en: Ireland (; ), or the Republic of Ireland, is a sovereign country in northwest Europe, occupying five-sixths of the island of Ireland. The country's capital and largest city is Dublin on the eastern side of the island. 4.75 million people live in the Dublin city metropolitan area, a third of the country. The kingdom shares its only land border with Northern Ireland, which is part of the United Kingdom. Apart from that, the country is surrounded by the Atlantic Ocean, the Celtic Sea to the south, St. George's Channel to the southeast, and the Irish Sea to the east. Ireland is a parliamentary republic. A parliament called the Oiractas consists of a lower house called the Dáil Éireann and an upper house called the Seanad Éireann. Although the president-elect (uvaktaran) is ceremonial, he has certain pre-eminent powers and duties.

passage_en: The 1960 United States presidential election was the 44th quadrennial presidential election, held on Tuesday, November 8, 1960. Republicans nominated incumbent Vice President Richard Nixon, while Democrats nominated John F. Kennedy, US Senator from Massachusetts. The incumbent president, Republican Dwight D. Eisenhower, is ineligible for re-election after being elected the maximum two times allowed by the Twenty-second Amendment; he was the first President affected by the change. This was the first presidential election in which voters in Alaska and Hawaii were able to participate, as they had become states in 1959.
